Business Brief -- Wang Laboratories Inc.:
   Deficit Narrowed Sharply
   In Fiscal Second Quarter
Wang said it recorded an operating profit before interest
and taxes of $3.9 million, its second consecutive operating
profit.
   Richard W. Miller, chairman and chief executive officer,
said that world economic and industry conditions "still pose
significant challenges" for computer makers. But he said he
was encouraged by the quarter's results, "which indicate that
Wang's revenues and financial performance remain stable
despite external adversities."
   Wang class B shares rose in very heavy American Stock
Exchange trading yesterday to close at $3.625, up 37.5 cents.